<item>
            <title>[JDK-8318720] G1: Memory leak in G1CodeRootSet after JDK-8315503</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8318720</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8315503&quot; title=&quot;G1: Code root scan causes long GC pauses due to imbalanced iteration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8315503&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8315503&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; replaced ResourceHashTable with ConcurrentHashTable.&lt;br/&gt;
When it tries to clear G1CodeRootSetHashTable, it calls ConcurrentHashTable:table.unsafe_reset(). &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The method has comments states:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;// Unsafe reset and resize the table. This method assumes that we&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;// want to clear and maybe resize the internal table without the&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;// overhead of clearing individual items in the table. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
So, if the table is not empty, then all entries in table are leaked.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
